<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id14371c5e-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s360ddd–2"><num value="360ddd–2">§ 360ddd–2.</num><heading> Inapplicability of drug fees to designated medical gases</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A designated medical gas, alone or in combination with another designated gas or gases (as medically appropriate) deemed under <ref href="/us/usc/t21/s360ddd–1">section 360ddd–1 of this title</ref> to have in effect an approved application shall not be assessed fees under section 379h(a) or 379j–12(a) of this title on the basis of such deemed approval.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id14371c5f-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/act/1938-06-25/ch675/s577">June 25, 1938, ch. 675, § 577</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/112/144/tXI/s1111">Pub. L. 112–144, title XI, § 1111</ref>, <date date="2012-07-09">July 9, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/1111">126 Stat. 1111</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/114/255/dA/tIII/s3101/a/2/T">Pub. L. 114–255, div. A, title III, § 3101(a)(2)(T)</ref>, <date date="2016-12-13">Dec. 13, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/1155">130 Stat. 1155</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
